u(x,t)=\frac{1}{2\sqrt{\pi k t}}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}g(y)\exp\frac{(x-y)^2}{4kt} dy.
\left. u_x \right|_{x=a}=0
g
x>a
g(x)=g(2a-x)
x<a
u(x,t)=\frac{1}{2\sqrt{\pi k t}}\left[\int_{a}^{\infty}g(y)\exp\frac{(x-y)^2}{4kt} dy + \int_{-\infty}^a g(2a-y)\exp\frac{(x-y)^2}{4kt} dy \right].
